---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <main class="faq-container">
    <header class="faq-header">
      <span class="faq-subtitle">Common Questions</span>
      <h1 class="faq-title">Frequently Asked Questions</h1>
    </header>

    <div class="faq-grid">
      <!-- Category: Booking & Logistics -->
      <section class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">Sessions & Logistics</h2>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">What happens if it rains/snows on the day of the shoot?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>Tokyo looks incredible when wet, especially at night with all those
            neon reflections. In the middle of a rain shower, however, things can be
            tricky. We offer a no-worries cancellation & refund of the shoot if the
            weather is severe. If weather unexpectedly becomes severe mid-shoot, we
            can shift to semi-covered corridors and alleys. </p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">Where do we meet to begin our shoot?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
            After booking, you will receive an email with the exact meeting location
            and any additional instructions for us to meet easily.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">Why do you limit short sessions to four people?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
            While a cutoff of four people might seem arbitrary, it's based on
            session pacing and available lighting (both ambient and flash).
            Restricting the group size ensures that every single person in the 
            session receives enough individual coverage without the shoot ever 
            feeling rushed or compromised.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">What is the 8-Hour "Human Interest" session?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>The Human Interest shoot is a full-day, documentary-style session. 
            Instead of a structured portrait shoot, I blend into your day and 
            document your experiences, movements, and interactions across the city 
            photographically, creating an authentic visual record of your time in 
            Tokyo.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">Do you spend hours/days editing photos from sessions?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>
            We offer photo editing as an a la carte service, but we generally don't
            recommend it to customers. Instead, we aim for proper lighting, exposure,
            and color in-camera. This approach is what allows us to deliver your
            photos to you immediately after the shoot finishes.
            </p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>

      <!-- Category: Payments, Changes & Business Terms (Bank Friendly) -->
      <section class="faq-section">
        <h2 class="faq-section__title">Rates, Payments & Cancellations</h2>
        
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">What are your payment and cancellation policies?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>Bookings are managed securely through Acuity Scheduling. We require
            payment in advance for all sessions. Cancellations must be made no later
            than 24 hours prior to a client's session. We implement these two policies
            to protect our photographers' time and schedule. Thank you in advance for
            respecting our policy.</p>
          </div>
        </details>

        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__question">Do you provide commercial licensing for the images?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__answer">
            <p>Our standard packages cover personal use (portfolios, social media, prints). If you require images for commercial use, advertising, or corporate branding, please contact us prior to booking to arrange a commercial licensing agreement.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </section>
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  .faq-container {
    max-width: 800px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: 4rem 1.5rem 6rem 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-header {
    text-align: center;
    margin-bottom: 4rem;
  }

  .faq-subtitle {
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.14em;
    color: var(--muted, #71717a);
    display: block;
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .faq-title {
    font-family: var(--serif-display, serif);
    font-size: 2.8rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: inherit;
    margin: 0;
  }

  .faq-grid {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 3.5rem;
  }

  .faq-section__title {
    font-size: 1.1rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.05em;
    color: var(--muted, #71717a);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(125, 125, 125, 0.15);
    padding-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  /* Native Accordion Styling */
  .faq-item {
    border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(125, 125, 125, 0.1);
    padding: 1.25rem 0;
    cursor: pointer;
  }

  /* Smooth layout states */
  .faq-item[open] {
    padding-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .faq-item__question {
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    font-weight: 500;
    list-style: none; /* Hides default browser disclosure triangle */
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    color: inherit;
    user-select: none;
  }

  /* Custom minimal indicator (+ / -) */
  .faq-item__question::after {
    content: '+';
    font-family: monospace;
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    color: var(--muted, #a1a1aa);
    transition: transform 0.2s ease;
  }

  .faq-item[open] .faq-item__question::after {
    content: '−';
  }

  /* Hide default Safari arrow */
  .faq-item__question::-webkit-details-marker {
    display: none;
  }

  .faq-item__answer {
    margin-top: 1rem;
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--muted, #a1a1aa);
    max-width: 600px;
  }

  .faq-item__answer p {
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* Responsive Adjustments */
  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .faq-container {
      padding: 2.5rem 1rem 4rem 1rem;
    }
    .faq-title {
      font-size: 2.1rem;
    }
    .faq-item__question {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
    }
    .faq-item__answer {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  }
</style>